{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1275,"text":"There's this quote by activist and punk\nrock musician Jello Biafra that I love."},{"time":6848,"text":"He says, \"Don't hate the media.\nBe the media.\""},{"time":11518,"text":"I'm an artist."},{"time":12880,"text":"I like working with media and technology\nbecause A, I'm familiar with them"},{"time":17778,"text":"and I like the power they hold."},{"time":19564,"text":"And B, I hate them and I'm terrified\nof the power they hold."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":25591,"text":"I remember watching, in 2003, an interview\nbetween Fox News host Tony Snow"},{"time":30925,"text":"and then-US Defense Secretary,\nDonald Rumsfeld."},{"time":35009,"text":"They were talking\nabout the recent invasion of Iraq,"},{"time":38138,"text":"and Rumsfeld is asked the question,"},{"time":41092,"text":"\"Well, we're hear about our body counts,"},{"time":43037,"text":"but we never hear about theirs, why?\""},{"time":47304,"text":"And Rumsfeld's answer is,"},{"time":51059,"text":"\"Well, we don't do body counts\non other people.\""},{"time":55000,"text":"Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":57220,"text":"It's estimated that between 150,000\nto one million Iraqis, civilians,"},{"time":62667,"text":"have died as a result\nof the US-led invasion in 2003."},{"time":67381,"text":"That number is in stark contrast with\nthe 4,486 US service members who died"},{"time":73721,"text":"during that same window of time."},{"time":76969,"text":"I wanted to do more than just bring\nawareness to this terrifying number."},{"time":80898,"text":"I wanted to create a monument\nfor the individual civilians"},{"time":83803,"text":"who died as a result of the invasion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87427,"text":"Monuments to war,\nsuch as Maya Lin's Vietnam Memorial,"},{"time":90928,"text":"are often enormous in scale."},{"time":92753,"text":"Very powerful and very one-sided."},{"time":96920,"text":"I wanted my monument to live\nin the world, and to circulate."},{"time":102642,"text":"I remember when I was a boy in school,"},{"time":105437,"text":"my teacher assigned us\nthis classic civics assignment"},{"time":109382,"text":"where you take a sheet of paper\nand you write a member of your government."},{"time":114195,"text":"And we were told,\nif we wrote a really good letter,"},{"time":116618,"text":"if we really thought about it,"},{"time":118116,"text":"we would get back more than just\na simple formed letter as a reply."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124144,"text":"This is my \"Notepad.\""},{"time":127338,"text":"What looks like an everyday,\nyellow legal tablet of paper"},{"time":130356,"text":"is actually a monument\nto the individual Iraqi civilians"},{"time":133983,"text":"that died as a result of the US invasion."},{"time":138726,"text":"\"Notepad\" is an act of protest\nand an act of commemoration"},{"time":142362,"text":"disguised as an everyday tablet of paper."},{"time":146522,"text":"The lines of the paper, when magnified,"},{"time":150364,"text":"are revealed to be micro-printed text"},{"time":152348,"text":"that contains the details, the names,\nthe dates and locations"},{"time":157118,"text":"of individual Iraqi civilians that died."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162091,"text":"So, for the last 5 years, I've been taking\npads of this paper, tons of this stuff,"},{"time":166372,"text":"and smuggling it\ninto the stationery supplies"},{"time":169840,"text":"of the United States\nand the Coalition governments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172555,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":173666,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":182095,"text":"I don't have to tell you guys this is not\nthe place to discuss how I did that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186110,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":188842,"text":"But also, I've been meeting one-on-one\nwith members and former members"},{"time":194086,"text":"of the so-called Coalition of the Willing,\nwho assisted in the invasion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199441,"text":"And so, whenever I can,\nI meet with one of them,"},{"time":201751,"text":"and I share the project with them."},{"time":203632,"text":"And last summer, I had the chance to meet"},{"time":205678,"text":"with former United States Attorney General\nand Torture Memo author, Alberto Gonzales."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212644,"text":"(Video) Matt Kenyon:\nMay I give this to you?"},{"time":214836,"text":"This is a special legal tablet."},{"time":216502,"text":"It's actually part\nof an ongoing art project."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219959,"text":"Alberto Gonzalez:\nThis is a special legal pad?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":222136,"text":"MK: Yes. You won't believe me,"},{"time":223638,"text":"but it's in the collection of the Museum\nof Modern Art; I'm an artist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227463,"text":"MK: And all of the lines\nof the paper are actually --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":230418,"text":"AG: Are they going to disappear?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":231982,"text":"MK: No, they're micro-printed text"},{"time":234253,"text":"that contains the names\nof individual Iraqi civilians"},{"time":238229,"text":"who have died since the invasion of Iraq."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241764,"text":"AG: Yeah. OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244508,"text":"AG: Thank you. MK: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246105,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":248406,"text":"The way he says \"thank you\"\nreally creeps me out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251139,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":253309,"text":"OK, so I'd like each of you\nto look under your chairs."},{"time":256524,"text":"There's an envelope."},{"time":260943,"text":"And please open it."},{"time":266014,"text":"The paper you're holding in your hand"},{"time":269047,"text":"contains the details of Iraqi civilians\nthat died as result of the invasion."},{"time":278115,"text":"I'd like you to use this paper\nand write a member of government."},{"time":282315,"text":"You can help to smuggle\nthis civilian body count"},{"time":286181,"text":"into government archives."},{"time":289084,"text":"Because every letter\nthat's sent in to the government,"},{"time":293053,"text":"and this is all across\nthe world, of course --"},{"time":295475,"text":"every letter that is sent in\nis archived, filed and recorded."},{"time":301183,"text":"Together, we can put this in the mailboxes\nand under the noses of people in power."},{"time":307429,"text":"Everything that's sent in"},{"time":309113,"text":"eventually becomes part of the permanent\narchive of our government,"},{"time":315148,"text":"our shared historical record."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318102,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319277,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":330015,"text":"Tom Rielly: So, tell me Matt,"},{"time":331999,"text":"how did this idea\ncome into your head, of \"Notepad\"?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":337954,"text":"Matt Kenyon: I'd just finished a project"},{"time":339960,"text":"that dealt with\nthe US Coalition side of the war"},{"time":343993,"text":"and it was a black armband that was called\nthe \"Improvised Empathetic Device\""},{"time":348355,"text":"which accumulated, in real time,"},{"time":351258,"text":"the names, ranks,\ncause of death and location"},{"time":355005,"text":"of US service members\nwho had died overseas,"},{"time":357811,"text":"and each time the Department of Defense\nor CENTCOM released their data,"},{"time":361777,"text":"it would stab me in the arm."},{"time":363817,"text":"And so, I became aware\nthat there was a spectacle"},{"time":366674,"text":"associated with our own people\nwho were dying overseas,"},{"time":369590,"text":"but a disproportionate\namount of casualties"},{"time":372277,"text":"were the civilian casualties."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374262,"text":"TR: Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375437,"text":"MK: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376628,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}